      • setIsDefault

        public ProvidersTypes.CreateSpec.Builder setIsDefault(java.lang.Boolean isDefault)
        Specifies whether the provider is the default provider. Setting getIsDefault() of current provider to True makes all other providers non-default. If no other providers created in this vCenter Server before, this parameter will be disregarded, and the provider will always be set to the default. Warning: This property is available as technical preview. It may be changed in a future release. If null the provider will be the default provider if it is the first provider that is created, and will not be the default provider otherwise.
        Parameters:
        isDefault - New value for the property.

      • setName

        public ProvidersTypes.CreateSpec.Builder setName(java.lang.String name)
        Friendly name for the provider. This must be unique, otherwise calling create() will throw InvalidArgument. Warning: This property is available as technical preview. It may be changed in a future release. If null, the server will use a UUID.
        Parameters:
        name - New value for the property.
